re different types of samadhi. Samadhi literally=\r\n means\nconcentration and focus of awareness. In its normal state, mind is\nv=\r\nibrating with too many thoughts and notions. In any state of samadhi,\nmost =\r\nof these thoughts and notions disappear and mind achieves a high\ndegree of =\r\nfocus.\n&gt;\n&gt; The focus can be on a physical object perceived through senses (=\r\ne.g.\nan idol or the physical sound of a mantra) or a subtle object perceive=\r\nd\nby the subtle perception (a deity or the subtle vibration of a mantra).\nT=\r\nhe focus can be on the gross/subtle object or on the act of perceiving\nthe =\r\nobject or on the perceiver (all the three exist within one&#39;s\nconsciousness =\r\nas three different things). One&#39;s self-awareness can\nidentify with one obje=\r\nct and focus its attention on another object (&quot;I\nam Rajarshi with so and so=\r\n qualities and I am aware of Bhairava with so\nand so qualities&quot;). Or, one&#39;s=\r\n self-awareness can identify with that\nobject (&quot;I am Bhairava with so and s=\r\no qualities&quot;). Please note that all\nthese samadhis are within the field of =\r\nduality. There is still a sense\nof &quot;this is I&quot; and &quot;this is the rest&quot;, i.e.=\r\n there is differentiation.\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; The next state is what most people=\r\n refer to as samadhi. This is a\nstate where mind is absorbed in non-dual Se=\r\nlf, i.e. without any\ndifferentiation. When there are no notions of &quot;this is=\r\n I&quot; and &quot;this is\nthe rest&quot;, there are no thoughts, no opposites and there i=\r\ns only\nSat-Chid-Ananda (the bliss of just being).\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; Now, let me=\r\n come to what Vimalananda says!\n&gt;\n&gt; The non-dual Self is Shiva (or Purusha =\r\nor Narayana). The field of\nduality is Shakti (or Prakriti or Narayani). Tho=\r\nugh one may normally\nthink that Shiva and Shakti are different, are they re=\r\nally different?!\n&gt;\n&gt; Because of our notion that Shiva and Shakti are differ=\r\nent, we can\neither be with Shakti or with Shiva at a time but not with both=\r\n at the\nsame time. A yogi who has objectification and the sense of &quot;this is=\r\n I&quot;\nand &quot;this is the rest&quot; is in the domain of Shakti. When one overcomes\no=\r\nbjectification and reaches non-dual samadhi, one is in the domain of\nShiva.=\r\n When one leaves that state and one&#39;s egosense (&quot;this is I&quot; and\n&quot;this is th=\r\ne rest&quot;) returns, one will *leave* the domain of Shiva and\nre-enter the fie=\r\nld of Shakti. One is prone to be deluded by duality\nagain! That is what Vim=\r\nalananda is saying.\n&gt;\n&gt; If one can be with Shiva *and* Shakti at the *same =\r\ntime*, then one is\nthen not enamored or deluded by any aspect of Shakti. Wh=\r\nen a small\naspect of Shakti enamors/deludes one (&quot;this is I&quot;, &quot;that is beau=\r\ntiful&quot;,\n&quot;that is ugly&quot;, &quot;I like that&quot; etc), one is unable to perceive the e=\r\nntire\nfield of Shakti. This is just like a person tied to a rock in the oce=\r\nan\nnot being able to swim the entire ocean. When one is not bound by any\nob=\r\nject in the field of Shakti and not attracted or repelled by anything,\nthen=\r\n one can navigate the entire field, i.e. all space-time\ncombinations. This =\r\nis possible only if one has perfect mastery over\nShakti. That comes only wh=\r\nen one has zero attachment to anything in the\nfield of Shakti. That comes o=\r\nnly when one is with Shiva enough and\neventually becomes like Shiva. If a y=\r\nogi reaches non-dual samadhi, stays\nin it for a long time and happens to co=\r\nme back to the field of duality,\nthen one may become like Shiva and work wi=\r\nth Shakti with zero attachment\nand perfect mastery. One is aware of the ent=\r\nire field of duality - all\nspaces and times - and yet unattached to anythin=\r\ng. That is because one\nperceives the underlying non-dual Self even as sense=\r\ns perceive various\nobjects of duality.\n&gt;\n&gt; For most people, this is out of =\r\nbounds. One either experiences\nnon-dual samadhi for a short duration and ca=\r\nnnot sustain it longer and\ncomes back to be deluded by duality again, or on=\r\ne stays in non-dual\nsamadhi for a long time and does not come back (like a =\r\nsalt doll that\ngoes to survey the depth of ocean melting in the ocean, to b=\r\norrow words\nfrom Ramakrishna Paramahamsa). Exceptions like Ramakrishna Para=\r\nmahamsa\nor Sai Baba, who spent enough time in non-dual samadhi and yet came=\r\n back\nto live in the world, are so rare in this age.\n&gt;\n&gt; * * *\n&gt;\n&gt; Let me p=\r\nut this in terms of Kundalini now. When Kundalini is in\nmoolaadhaara, our s=\r\nelf-awareness identifies with the physical body and\nis aware of the physica=\r\nl world around us. As Kundalini goes to various\nplaces in the subtle body (=\r\nthere are thousands of nadis and chakras!),\none is aware of various realiti=\r\nes that are out there in this universe.\nFor example, one world (realm of aw=\r\nareness) may be reverberating with\nthe sound of a particular beejaakshara a=\r\nnd filled with a particular\nlight and every being in that world may be a sm=\r\nall particle in that\nlight reverberating with that sound. Like that, there =\r\nare many worlds\nout there (within us) and one can enter a samadhi through a=\r\nny of them,\nwhen Kundalini reaches a corresponding place.\n&gt;\n&gt; When Kundalin=\r\ni reaches sahasrara, one&#39;s self-awareness is with Shiva.\nShakti loses herse=\r\nlf to Shiva and there is no objectification that is\nthe hallmark of Shakti.=\r\n If shakti comes back from sahasrara to a lower\nchakra, one&#39;s self-awarenes=\r\ns is again deluded by duality. However, if\nshakti comes back from sahasrara=\r\n to mooladhara *accompanied by* Shiva,\nthen one is aware of duality and non=\r\n-dual Self at the same time. One\nlives as a liberated sage, using the body =\r\nas an instrument to fulfil the\nwill of Nature (since there is no longer any=\r\n individual will).\n&gt;\n&gt; Best regards,\n&gt; Narasimha\n&gt;\n------------------------=\r\n-----------------------------------------------\n&gt; Free Jyotish Software, Fr=\r\nee Jyotish MP3 Lessons, Free Jyotish\ntextbook,\n&gt; Free &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritu=\r\nal manuals for short Homam and Pitri\nTarpana:\n&gt; http://www.VedicAstrologer.=\r\norg\n&gt; Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org\n&gt; Spiritualit=\r\ny: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom\n&gt; Jyotish writings: http://gr=\r\noups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings\n&gt;\n------------------------------------=\r\n-----------------------------------\n&gt;\n&gt; ---- hramalingam@... wrote:\n&gt; &gt; The=\r\n Samadi is nothing but killing the mind and the entire thought\nprocess\n&gt; &gt; =\r\nThis will answer all your questions\n&gt; &gt; Sent from my BlackBerry=C2=AE on Re=\r\nliance Mobile, India&#39;s No. 1\nNetwork. Go for it!\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; -----Original Mess=\r\nage-----\n&gt; &gt; From: rajarshi nandy rajarshi14@...\n&gt; &gt; Sender: vedic-wisdom@y=\r\nahoogroups.com\n&gt; &gt; Date: Thu, 14 Oct 2010 13:53:33\n&gt; &gt; To: vedic-astrology@=\r\nyahoogroups.com; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\n&gt; &gt; Reply-To: vedic-wisdom@ya=\r\nhoogroups.com\n&gt; &gt; Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: [vedic-astrology] Re: what do=\r\nes PURITY\nMean\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Namaste,\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Can someone kindly explain what kin=\r\nd of samadhi does the following\nspiritual\n&gt; &gt; experience denote, (quoted fr=\r\nom Vimalanada&#39;s statement in the Aghora\nbook)?\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; &quot;All these swamis ta=\r\nlk about samadhi as the highest goal, but I\nthink they are\n&gt; &gt; fools. What =\r\nis the use of these spurting samadhis, anyway? Fine you\ngo off into\n&gt; &gt; a t=\r\nrance, but when you drop back down to earth, you are just as you\nwere befor=\r\ne.\n&gt; &gt; That sort of sam